        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-11-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-10-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="424" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d424">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_NEA1">NEA</gloss> Files: Lot 55–D36</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Statement by the United States and the United Kingdom
                        Groups</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1947-11-07T23:59:59-05:00" notBefore="1947-10-16T00:00:00-05:00">undated</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Cyprus</hi>
                </p>
                <p>It was the opinion of both groups that in existing circumstances the maintenance
                    of Cyprus as a British base area would be in the interest of Middle Eastern
                    security and world peace. This would not, however, preclude the possibility of
                    reviewing the status of Cyprus at some future time.</p>
            </div>
